%T A397402 3051970920,41912154576,618187067448,9745330336704,163502244052584,
%U A397402 2908579765827648,54680702467271928,1083188959780303776,22549856759646039240,492172063135495855056
%N A397402 Number of permutations p of 1,2,...,n satisfying p(i+2)-p(i)<>3 for all 1<=i<=n-2.
%C A397402 a(n) is the number of permutations of {1,...,n} such that no two elements exactly 2 apart in position differ by exactly 3.
%H A397402 Jaideep Padhi, <a href="/A397402/b397402.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..88</a>
%H A397402 George Spahn and Doron Zeilberger, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.02550">Counting Permutations Where The Difference Between Entries Located r Places Apart Can never be s</a>, arXiv:2211.02550 [math.CO], 2022.
%F A397402 a(n) = Sum over tilings of {1,...,n} by the inclusion-exclusion method of Spahn and Zeilberger (2022), arXiv:2211.02550.
%e A397402 a(3) = 6: all 6 permutations of {1,2,3} are valid since the only constraint would require p(3)-p(1) != 3, and no permutation of {1,2,3} has p(3)-p(1) = 3 (the maximum difference is 2).
%e A397402 a(4) = 20: 1234, 1324, 1423, 1432, 2143, 2314, 2341, 2413, 2431, 3142, 3214, 3241, 3412, 3421, 4123, 4132, 4213, 4231, 4312, 4321.
%Y A397402 Cf. A189281, A189282, A189283, A189284.
%K A397402 nonn
